WEBVTT

1
00:01:03.150 --> 00:01:04.629
Don't stop.

2
00:01:04.760 --> 00:01:08.198
I love your hands on me.

3
00:01:14.683 --> 00:01:15.901
Hello?

4
00:01:23.039 --> 00:01:25.346
Titus. what?

5
00:01:25.476 --> 00:01:27.913
"I love your hands on me."

6
00:01:28.044 --> 00:01:29.741
Where have I heard that before?

7
00:01:35.182 --> 00:01:37.532
You know. I thought...

8
00:01:37.619 --> 00:01:40.317
that when we moved here
things would be different.

9
00:01:40.448 --> 00:01:43.015
I thought that this would be

10
00:01:43.146 --> 00:01:44.386
a fresh start for our marriage.

11
00:01:44.452 --> 00:01:46.062
- I'm gonna be late.
- Titus!

12
00:01:46.149 --> 00:01:47.469
What do you want from me. Amara?

13
00:01:49.631 --> 00:01:53.330
I want you to stop punishing me.

14
00:01:53.461 --> 00:01:57.160
Baby... I want you to touch me.

15
00:01:59.075 --> 00:02:01.295
I love you. babe...

16
00:02:01.425 --> 00:02:02.600
more than life itself.

17
00:02:02.731 --> 00:02:04.646
Now. I know I made one mistake.

18
00:02:04.776 --> 00:02:07.039
I've told you a thousand times
he meant nothing...

19
00:02:08.737 --> 00:02:11.305
- Who meant nothing?
- Get off me.

20
00:02:11.435 --> 00:02:13.829
You can't even say his name.
can you?

21
00:02:13.959 --> 00:02:15.657
It's Damian Collins...

22
00:02:15.744 --> 00:02:18.442
in case you forgot.
because I never will.

23
00:02:37.113 --> 00:02:39.115
Tracy! Tracy!

24
00:02:40.769 --> 00:02:43.424
Tracy. wake up!
Mother's waiting.

25
00:02:43.554 --> 00:02:45.165
Tracy. would you stop playing?

26
00:02:47.428 --> 00:02:48.559
Tracy!

27
00:02:55.436 --> 00:02:56.611
Tracy?

28
00:02:56.741 --> 00:02:57.873
Tracy. honey. wake up!

29
00:02:58.003 --> 00:02:59.222
Tracy. wake up!

30
00:02:59.353 --> 00:03:01.093
Honey. wake up. please. wake up!

31
00:03:01.181 --> 00:03:03.748
Wake... Evan. call 911!

32
00:03:03.879 --> 00:03:06.098
Honey. wake up. Tracy. please.
wake up. wake up. honey.

33
00:03:06.229 --> 00:03:07.622
Please. you were doing so well.

34
00:03:07.752 --> 00:03:10.015
- It's no use. Stephanie.
- She's dead.

35
00:03:10.146 --> 00:03:11.887
Tracy. wake up! Wake up!

36
00:03:12.017 --> 00:03:13.018
And you're next.

37
00:03:18.894 --> 00:03:21.157
Evan. Evan. no. please!

38
00:03:21.288 --> 00:03:22.288
No!

39
00:04:20.738 --> 00:04:22.305
Good morning.

40
00:04:22.436 --> 00:04:24.525
You sleep okay last night?

41
00:04:24.655 --> 00:04:26.309
- Perfectly fine.
- Why do you ask?

42
00:04:26.440 --> 00:04:27.832
You were a bit restless.

43
00:04:27.963 --> 00:04:29.593
I was worried Constance
might have secretly replaced

44
00:04:29.617 --> 00:04:31.017
our sheets
with lower thread counts.

45
00:04:32.446 --> 00:04:33.969
I appreciate
your concern. darling.

46
00:04:34.099 --> 00:04:36.101
but I can assure you
I'm perfectly refreshed.

47
00:04:37.886 --> 00:04:38.886
Good morning. princess.

48
00:04:38.930 --> 00:04:40.280
Good morning. Dad.

49
00:04:40.410 --> 00:04:41.866
She's out of bed
before the evening news.

50
00:04:41.890 --> 00:04:43.152
Will wonders never cease?

51
00:04:43.283 --> 00:04:44.523
Cut her some slack. Stephanie.

52
00:04:44.632 --> 00:04:45.981
Spelman's on break.

53
00:04:46.111 --> 00:04:48.031
The child can afford
to sleep in a few more days.

54
00:04:48.157 --> 00:04:50.812
I couldn't wait to get out
on breaks when I was your age.

55
00:04:50.942 --> 00:04:52.703
I would rush right home
to work for your grandfather

56
00:04:52.727 --> 00:04:54.381
at his firm.

57
00:04:54.468 --> 00:04:57.079
I had something that was known
back then as self-determination.

58
00:04:57.166 --> 00:04:58.950
You should Google it some time.

59
00:04:59.081 --> 00:05:00.256
What's Google?

60
00:05:02.171 --> 00:05:05.217
Not that you asked. Mom. but
I was up late learning my lines.

61
00:05:05.305 --> 00:05:06.745
You're in another play.
sweetheart?

62
00:05:06.784 --> 00:05:08.849
You guys never listen when
I tell you about my life.

63
00:05:08.873 --> 00:05:10.919
I told you. I got the role
of Lady in Blue

64
00:05:11.049 --> 00:05:12.529
in "For Colored Girls."

65
00:05:12.660 --> 00:05:14.681
That's right! I'm gonna
call your brother tonight.

66
00:05:14.705 --> 00:05:16.074
Maybe Trey can come
to your opening.

67
00:05:16.098 --> 00:05:17.621
Perfect.

68
00:05:17.752 --> 00:05:20.058
Carly. you know that
your father and I support you

69
00:05:20.189 --> 00:05:21.495
in everything that you do.

70
00:05:21.582 --> 00:05:23.932
but at some point
you might want to consider

71
00:05:24.062 --> 00:05:26.282
a more practical major
than theatre studies.

72
00:05:26.369 --> 00:05:29.459
You mean like pre-law. so I
can follow in your footsteps?

73
00:05:29.590 --> 00:05:31.505
And your father's.
and your grandfather's.

74
00:05:31.592 --> 00:05:33.637
And my great-grandfather
Samuel Perkins.

75
00:05:33.768 --> 00:05:34.856
I know. Mom.

76
00:05:34.943 --> 00:05:36.553
I've heard the pitch
a thousand times.

77
00:05:36.684 --> 00:05:40.340
Sweetheart. how are things
going with you and Khalil?

78
00:05:40.470 --> 00:05:42.037
- Khalil is...
- I think it's wonderful

79
00:05:42.167 --> 00:05:44.561
that you're seeing
Marvin and Marilyn Barnes's son.

80
00:05:44.692 --> 00:05:47.782
Looked like you two
were getting close.

81
00:05:47.912 --> 00:05:50.567
It's really not
that serious. Dad.

82
00:05:50.698 --> 00:05:52.656
He just seems like
a good match for you.

83
00:05:52.787 --> 00:05:54.286
I've been trying to convince
Marvin to move

84
00:05:54.310 --> 00:05:56.486
his manufacturing plants
from China to Atlanta.

85
00:05:56.617 --> 00:05:58.116
It would be a huge boost
for the city's economy.

86
00:05:58.140 --> 00:05:59.315
I'll call Marilyn.

87
00:05:59.446 --> 00:06:00.686
I'm gonna leave you two at it.

88
00:06:00.795 --> 00:06:02.579
Things are crazy at city hall.

89
00:06:02.666 --> 00:06:05.106
Abandoning me to the task of
charting our daughter's course.

90
00:06:05.190 --> 00:06:06.540
per usual. I see?

91
00:06:06.670 --> 00:06:08.510
Well. you run everyone's
lives so well. babe.

92
00:06:10.805 --> 00:06:12.110
Bye.

93
00:06:19.857 --> 00:06:22.469
Hey. whee!

94
00:06:22.599 --> 00:06:25.254
Keisha. girl. turn that up!

95
00:06:25.385 --> 00:06:28.823
This used to be my jam.

96
00:06:28.953 --> 00:06:30.593
Y'all know he was
singing about me. right?

97
00:06:34.959 --> 00:06:36.308
If I'd known there was a party.

98
00:06:36.396 --> 00:06:38.702
I'd worn my dancing shoes.

99
00:06:38.833 --> 00:06:40.530
What the hell
do you want. Peters?

100
00:06:40.661 --> 00:06:42.793
Ya know. you're one
hostile lady. Rondell.

101
00:06:42.924 --> 00:06:44.012
Ms. Lancaster.

102
00:06:44.142 --> 00:06:45.361
You don't know me like that.

103
00:06:45.492 --> 00:06:48.625
Fine. Ms. Lancaster.
you know why I'm here.

104
00:06:48.756 --> 00:06:50.584
I already told you
I'm not selling.

105
00:06:50.714 --> 00:06:52.629
You're not gonna have
a choice much longer.

106
00:06:52.716 --> 00:06:53.780
The English Rose development's
going to happen

107
00:06:53.804 --> 00:06:55.173
whether you like it or not.
Rondell.

108
00:06:55.197 --> 00:06:58.026
You could sell to me now.
and get a good deal.

109
00:06:58.156 --> 00:07:00.047
or I can wait until the city
snatches up the entire block

110
00:07:00.071 --> 00:07:01.595
by enforcing
the eminent domain order.

111
00:07:01.725 --> 00:07:03.510
I can read. Peters.

112
00:07:03.640 --> 00:07:06.053
That court order said I got two
months to get enough signatures

113
00:07:06.077 --> 00:07:07.601
for injunctive relief.

114
00:07:07.731 --> 00:07:09.211
You don't even
know what that means.

115
00:07:09.298 --> 00:07:11.082
It means more time to stop
your smug ass

116
00:07:11.213 --> 00:07:13.041
from gutting this neighborhood.

117
00:07:13.171 --> 00:07:15.043
For the life of me.
I'll never understand

118
00:07:15.173 --> 00:07:17.872
why you're fighting this hard.
Is this dive even up to code?

119
00:07:18.002 --> 00:07:22.006
I'd hate... for it
to catch on fire.

120
00:07:22.093 --> 00:07:23.965
I bet your poor old man
would have a hard time

121
00:07:24.095 --> 00:07:27.621
making it out alive.

122
00:07:27.751 --> 00:07:30.058
I suggest you turn
your pasty self around

123
00:07:30.188 --> 00:07:32.321
and leave my restaurant
while you still can.

124
00:07:34.541 --> 00:07:35.716
And Peters.

125
00:07:37.544 --> 00:07:40.982
If you ever decide to
threaten me or my family again.

126
00:07:41.112 --> 00:07:43.680
I'll stick this blade
so far up yo' ass.

127
00:07:43.811 --> 00:07:45.813
you will need a colonoscopy
to find it.

128
00:07:45.943 --> 00:07:47.379
Do you hear me?

129
00:07:54.909 --> 00:07:57.999
One thing about
making threats. Rondell.

130
00:07:58.129 --> 00:08:02.394
you have to be prepared
to follow through.

131
00:08:02.525 --> 00:08:04.701
Now you be careful out there.

132
00:08:04.832 --> 00:08:08.575
Atlanta can be
a rough city after dark.

133
00:08:18.062 --> 00:08:21.065
Cheap-ass suit.

134
00:08:29.030 --> 00:08:30.030
Hey!

135
00:08:30.074 --> 00:08:31.074
Hey.

136
00:08:32.816 --> 00:08:33.948
Is that a new case?

137
00:08:34.078 --> 00:08:36.559
FBI's convinced several
higher ups

138
00:08:36.690 --> 00:08:39.388
in the mayor's cabinet
are on the take.

139
00:08:39.519 --> 00:08:43.305
We're talking allegations of
patronage. money laundering.

140
00:08:43.435 --> 00:08:45.699
embezzlement. you name it.

141
00:08:47.918 --> 00:08:49.920
You think Mayor Lancaster's
in on it?

142
00:08:50.051 --> 00:08:51.966
That's what I need you find out.

143
00:08:53.228 --> 00:08:54.534
I don't know. Karen.

144
00:08:54.664 --> 00:08:56.884
I... I went to college
with the guy's wife.

145
00:08:56.971 --> 00:08:58.755
Even better.

146
00:08:58.886 --> 00:09:00.428
We can use your history
with Stephanie Lancaster

147
00:09:00.452 --> 00:09:01.845
to our advantage.

148
00:09:01.976 --> 00:09:04.282
I wanna cast a wide net
on this one.

149
00:09:04.413 --> 00:09:07.068
Take down as many
crooked bureaucrats as possible.

150
00:09:08.939 --> 00:09:10.830
And I don't need to tell you
what a case like this

151
00:09:10.854 --> 00:09:11.986
would do for your career.

152
00:09:12.116 --> 00:09:13.116
No.

153
00:09:13.161 --> 00:09:14.945
And mine.

154
00:09:15.076 --> 00:09:17.818
Look. Amara. I pulled
a lot of strings to get you

155
00:09:17.948 --> 00:09:19.820
transferred in from Birmingham.

156
00:09:19.950 --> 00:09:23.214
I know. Karen.
and I appreciate that. but...

157
00:09:23.345 --> 00:09:24.999
But nothing.

158
00:09:25.129 --> 00:09:27.567
Show me how much you appreciate
it by taking the damn case.

159
00:09:29.830 --> 00:09:32.093
I'm sorry. Karen. I'm just...

160
00:09:32.223 --> 00:09:34.661
I'm not the right woman
for the job.

161
00:09:47.325 --> 00:09:49.414
- Signature's all we need.
- Got it.

162
00:09:53.201 --> 00:09:54.637
Hi. Mother.

163
00:09:54.768 --> 00:09:56.397
I didn't know you were
stopping by the office today.

164
00:09:56.421 --> 00:09:58.501
Well. your father was
gracious enough to let me use

165
00:09:58.598 --> 00:10:02.819
one of the conference rooms for
some last-minute gala planning.

166
00:10:02.906 --> 00:10:07.215
This year promises to be
our grandest evening yet.

167
00:10:09.913 --> 00:10:11.175
Mwah.

168
00:10:11.306 --> 00:10:13.613
You have a wonderful day.
sweetheart.

169
00:10:13.700 --> 00:10:16.137
Mwah. Mwah.

170
00:10:16.224 --> 00:10:17.747
You two play nice.

171
00:10:23.318 --> 00:10:26.060
So...

172
00:10:26.190 --> 00:10:28.715
how are things coming
with the Purifoy class action?

173
00:10:28.845 --> 00:10:30.685
Just running down the last
of the plaintiffs.

174
00:10:30.717 --> 00:10:31.500
then we can file.

175
00:10:31.587 --> 00:10:33.023
Good.

176
00:10:33.154 --> 00:10:36.548
I put one foot up
Purifoy's ass 25 years ago.

177
00:10:36.636 --> 00:10:39.073
It's time for the other one.

178
00:10:39.203 --> 00:10:41.815
You know. Daddy.
you'd have a lot more time

179
00:10:41.902 --> 00:10:43.817
to help Mother
with the foundation

180
00:10:43.947 --> 00:10:45.707
if you cut back on your workload
at the firm.

181
00:10:45.732 --> 00:10:47.168
Here it comes.

182
00:10:47.255 --> 00:10:48.822
I'm serious. Daddy.

183
00:10:48.952 --> 00:10:50.954
You've been talking about
retiring for years.

184
00:10:51.085 --> 00:10:52.216
Why not now?

185
00:10:52.303 --> 00:10:53.565
The firm's doing well.

186
00:10:53.696 --> 00:10:56.568
And I can take over
the day-to-day management.

187
00:10:56.699 --> 00:10:58.919
You can't even keep that
bottom feeder of a husband

188
00:10:59.049 --> 00:11:00.849
of yours in line.
and you want me to trust you

189
00:11:00.964 --> 00:11:03.140
with my entire law firm?

190
00:11:03.271 --> 00:11:05.795
The only reason I'm still
married to that "bottom feeder"

191
00:11:05.926 --> 00:11:07.643
is because you talked
me out of divorcing him.

192
00:11:07.667 --> 00:11:08.929
So it's my fault?

193
00:11:09.059 --> 00:11:10.539
You said that
having a son-in-law

194
00:11:10.670 --> 00:11:12.976
in the Mayor's office
would be good for business.

195
00:11:13.107 --> 00:11:15.239
that the Carlisles
would run the city.

196
00:11:15.370 --> 00:11:18.286
All I had to do was play my part
as the dutiful First Lady.

197
00:11:18.373 --> 00:11:20.288
Well. I did what you asked.

198
00:11:20.418 --> 00:11:21.593
Evan's the mayor.

199
00:11:21.724 --> 00:11:23.683
And now I want
more than photo-ops

200
00:11:23.770 --> 00:11:25.554
and ribbon-cutting ceremonies.

201
00:11:25.685 --> 00:11:29.514
It's time you handed
Carlisle Perkins over to me.

202
00:11:29.645 --> 00:11:30.994
You lack certain skills.

203
00:11:32.866 --> 00:11:36.913
And by skills. do you mean
a penis and a pair of testicles?

204
00:11:37.000 --> 00:11:38.325
So I can strut around
the locker room

205
00:11:38.349 --> 00:11:40.177
sharing secrets
with the good ol' boys?

206
00:11:40.264 --> 00:11:43.398
See? That's exactly why
you're not ready.

207
00:11:43.528 --> 00:11:46.096
You are a brilliant attorney.
Stephanie.

208
00:11:46.227 --> 00:11:48.185
but you've got a lot to learn.

209
00:11:48.272 --> 00:11:51.188
And it's a good thing I plan
to stick around to teach you.

210
00:11:51.319 --> 00:11:54.191
Dammit. Daddy. I could take
this firm global if you would

211
00:11:54.322 --> 00:11:57.934
just step aside and let me
run things my way.

212
00:11:58.021 --> 00:12:02.286
Is that why you've been
wining and dining.

213
00:12:02.417 --> 00:12:06.073
The senior partners
behind my back. sweetheart?

214
00:12:08.118 --> 00:12:11.078
Planning a little coup. are we?

215
00:12:11.208 --> 00:12:14.690
Stephanie. there is nothing that
happens in my firm

216
00:12:14.821 --> 00:12:16.518
or in my town
that I don't know about.

217
00:12:16.648 --> 00:12:18.128
And don't you ever forget that.

218
00:12:18.259 --> 00:12:20.478
Now you have one job
right now. okay?

219
00:12:20.609 --> 00:12:23.351
Get that ungrateful
husband of yours to play ball.

220
00:12:23.481 --> 00:12:27.137
Stop schmoozing and scheming.
trying to pull some power play.

221
00:12:27.268 --> 00:12:29.531
I get a whiff of any more
of your back-room maneuvers.

222
00:12:29.661 --> 00:12:32.708
and you are out on your ass.
daughter or not.

223
00:12:46.896 --> 00:12:48.768
We'll just see
about that. Daddy.

224
00:12:50.726 --> 00:12:52.399
Well. I think this
all looks good. Titus.

225
00:12:52.423 --> 00:12:53.947
Appreciate your time.

226
00:12:58.168 --> 00:13:00.083
- We'll talk later.
- Okay. Bye.

227
00:13:02.172 --> 00:13:06.960
Titus. that meeting
couldn't have gone any better.

228
00:13:07.047 --> 00:13:09.223
You had the board eating
right out of your hands.

229
00:13:09.353 --> 00:13:11.529
They seem like a good group.
Mr. Purifoy.

230
00:13:11.616 --> 00:13:14.663
Now. I hope we've impressed
on you how important it is

231
00:13:14.750 --> 00:13:16.926
that we stop
this class action lawsuit.

232
00:13:17.057 --> 00:13:18.057
Yes. sir.

233
00:13:18.145 --> 00:13:19.165
Stephen Carlisle has been out

234
00:13:19.189 --> 00:13:21.365
to destroy my business
for decades.

235
00:13:21.496 --> 00:13:24.325
Now his bitch of a daughter's
taken up the charge.

236
00:13:24.455 --> 00:13:28.242
Now. they act like we're
dope dealers peddling smack.

237
00:13:28.372 --> 00:13:30.331
Purifoy Pharmaceuticals
manufactures

238
00:13:30.461 --> 00:13:33.203
an FDA approved pain medication
for God's sake.

239
00:13:33.334 --> 00:13:36.467
We make Limodol to help people.
not hurt 'em.

240
00:13:36.598 --> 00:13:39.819
Don't worry. sir. I plan
to mount a vigorous defense.

241
00:13:39.949 --> 00:13:42.082
You know. I got
a good mind to skip

242
00:13:42.212 --> 00:13:45.128
that self-serving. Carlisle
ego fest of a gala this year.

243
00:13:45.259 --> 00:13:47.261
Mr. Purifoy.
it'll be a PR nightmare

244
00:13:47.391 --> 00:13:50.133
if you don't make an appearance
with this lawsuit looming.

245
00:13:50.264 --> 00:13:51.961
I think you and your family
should go.

246
00:13:52.092 --> 00:13:53.310
Donate some money.

247
00:13:53.441 --> 00:13:55.312
Show the people of Atlanta that
the Purifoys

248
00:13:55.399 --> 00:13:58.446
are heartbroken
over this opioid epidemic.

249
00:14:00.361 --> 00:14:02.537
See. I knew I made
the right decision when I lured

250
00:14:02.667 --> 00:14:05.235
you away from solo practice
and into the big leagues.

251
00:14:05.366 --> 00:14:06.802
Nothing against Birmingham.

252
00:14:06.933 --> 00:14:10.414
but you belong in a major city
like Atlanta.

253
00:14:10.545 --> 00:14:13.809
A young brother like you's gonna
go far in a city like this.

254
00:14:13.940 --> 00:14:15.724
- A young brother?
- Damn straight.

255
00:14:15.811 --> 00:14:17.291
Especially with my backing.

256
00:14:17.421 --> 00:14:20.990
I mean. it's no secret Atlanta
is a black city. Titus.

257
00:14:21.077 --> 00:14:22.862
I mean. an ol' cracker like me
can only reach

258
00:14:22.992 --> 00:14:25.995
a certain level of prominence.
even with all my money.

259
00:14:26.082 --> 00:14:29.085
But you and me together...

260
00:14:29.216 --> 00:14:31.392
we're gonna be unstoppable.

261
00:14:31.479 --> 00:14:35.352
In fact. I want
you and your wife at my table.

262
00:14:35.483 --> 00:14:36.658
Of course. sir.

263
00:14:38.790 --> 00:14:40.159
Well. I better get ready
for my next meeting.

264
00:14:40.183 --> 00:14:41.184
You do that.

265
00:14:44.318 --> 00:14:45.885
You watch out for her.

266
00:14:46.015 --> 00:14:47.712
She's as wicked
as a rattlesnake.

267
00:14:52.587 --> 00:14:54.241
Hi. how are you? Hi.

268
00:14:54.371 --> 00:14:56.286
Hi. good morning. Hi.

269
00:14:57.853 --> 00:14:59.724
Good morning.

270
00:14:59.855 --> 00:15:03.076
I hope the Purifoys
sent someone competent.

271
00:15:03.163 --> 00:15:04.164
You tell me.

272
00:15:07.515 --> 00:15:09.952
Titus Hughes.

273
00:15:10.039 --> 00:15:11.084
Good morning. counselor.

274
00:15:14.043 --> 00:15:15.784
What are you doing here?

275
00:15:15.871 --> 00:15:17.264
Admiring the view.

276
00:15:17.394 --> 00:15:18.743
I seem to recall you

277
00:15:18.830 --> 00:15:23.096
being easily distracted
by other views.

278
00:15:23.183 --> 00:15:24.227
How is Amara?

279
00:15:24.358 --> 00:15:25.185
She's well.

280
00:15:25.315 --> 00:15:26.490
Thank you for asking.

281
00:15:26.621 --> 00:15:28.536
It looks like she's
taking good care of you.

282
00:15:28.623 --> 00:15:29.943
Can I take that as a compliment?

283
00:15:30.016 --> 00:15:31.539
More of an observation.

284
00:15:31.669 --> 00:15:33.109
but you can take it
however you like.

285
00:15:35.064 --> 00:15:37.327
You always said you'd
run this place one day.

286
00:15:37.414 --> 00:15:39.175
And you always said you'd
dedicate your life

287
00:15:39.199 --> 00:15:41.244
to fighting
for the less fortunate.

288
00:15:41.331 --> 00:15:44.291
Now here you are
in my conference room

289
00:15:44.421 --> 00:15:47.859
all set to defend
a soulless corporation.

290
00:15:47.990 --> 00:15:49.774
What can I say? People change.

291
00:15:49.861 --> 00:15:51.254
Not all people.

292
00:15:53.517 --> 00:15:56.085
You look good. Stephanie.

293
00:15:56.172 --> 00:15:58.958
You do understand that flattery

294
00:15:59.088 --> 00:16:01.873
won't make me go any easier
on you in court?

295
00:16:02.004 --> 00:16:05.877
Well. before we go
all John Grisham on one another.

296
00:16:05.965 --> 00:16:09.272
you think an old friend
can get a hug?

297
00:16:09.403 --> 00:16:12.536
Titus. you and I were
a lot of things to one another...

298
00:16:12.623 --> 00:16:15.409
Lovers. competitors.

299
00:16:15.539 --> 00:16:16.888
enemies...

300
00:16:18.760 --> 00:16:20.370
but never quite friends.

301
00:16:20.501 --> 00:16:23.156
I guess that was the problem?

302
00:16:23.286 --> 00:16:24.592
You tell me.

303
00:16:30.685 --> 00:16:32.358
I must admit. there's still
something about you

304
00:16:32.382 --> 00:16:33.383
after all these years.

305
00:16:36.169 --> 00:16:38.475
However...

306
00:16:38.606 --> 00:16:40.129
I wanna be clear.

307
00:16:40.260 --> 00:16:44.829
I plan to dismantle
Purifoy Pharmaceuticals

308
00:16:44.916 --> 00:16:48.485
brick by brick.

309
00:16:48.616 --> 00:16:51.227
Give me your best.
Stephanie Carlisle.

310
00:16:51.358 --> 00:16:54.056
It's Lancaster now.

311
00:16:54.143 --> 00:16:57.103
And it's my worst
that should concern you.

312
00:17:34.401 --> 00:17:36.011
Alright. hold on. I'll be back.

313
00:17:41.930 --> 00:17:44.063
What was so urgent

314
00:17:44.193 --> 00:17:47.109
you had to see me today.
Lancaster?

315
00:17:47.240 --> 00:17:49.590
I heard about the visits
you've been paying my sister.

316
00:17:49.720 --> 00:17:50.720
I want you to stop.

317
00:17:52.462 --> 00:17:54.725
The thing about family... they
can either

318
00:17:54.812 --> 00:17:57.424
propel us to greatness. or they
can be our Achilles heel.

319
00:17:57.511 --> 00:17:59.643
Spare me the Greek philosophy.
Peters.

320
00:17:59.774 --> 00:18:01.167
Leave Rondell out of this.

321
00:18:01.297 --> 00:18:02.927
I'm not sure you comprehend
what's at stake here.

322
00:18:02.951 --> 00:18:04.363
I need that entire block
in The Banks

323
00:18:04.387 --> 00:18:05.538
to make this development work.

324
00:18:05.562 --> 00:18:08.087
And you need me
to remain in your corner

325
00:18:08.174 --> 00:18:09.934
if you ever wanna make
your dream of becoming

326
00:18:10.045 --> 00:18:13.570
the first black governor
of Georgia a reality.

327
00:18:13.701 --> 00:18:15.485
Relax. Peters.

328
00:18:15.616 --> 00:18:17.376
There's no reason we can't
all get what we want.

329
00:18:17.400 --> 00:18:18.943
Here's the difference
between you and me. Lancaster.

330
00:18:18.967 --> 00:18:20.316
You're a patient man.

331
00:18:20.403 --> 00:18:21.448
I'm not.

332
00:18:21.578 --> 00:18:22.666
I'll handle my sister.

333
00:18:22.753 --> 00:18:24.059
I know one of us better.

334
00:18:27.018 --> 00:18:29.195
See you at your family's gala.

335
00:18:29.325 --> 00:18:32.023
You know how much I love
giving back to the community.

336
00:18:43.774 --> 00:18:45.950
You understand
I must look perfect?

337
00:18:46.081 --> 00:18:48.039
Trust me. Stephanie.
you are going to be

338
00:18:48.170 --> 00:18:50.520
the most beautiful woman
in the room.

339
00:18:50.651 --> 00:18:53.132
Mayor Lancaster won't be
able take his eyes off you.

340
00:18:55.264 --> 00:18:56.700
Did I say something wrong?

341
00:18:56.831 --> 00:18:58.963
This isn't about him. Bella.

342
00:18:59.050 --> 00:19:01.879
It's about honoring
the memory of my sister.

343
00:19:02.010 --> 00:19:03.751
Besides.
when you've been married

344
00:19:03.881 --> 00:19:08.712
as long as Evan and I have.
you don't expect to be noticed.

345
00:19:08.843 --> 00:19:10.410
What about your love life?

346
00:19:10.497 --> 00:19:12.325
Who are you bringing
to the gala?

347
00:19:12.455 --> 00:19:14.805
I'm taking Roderick.

348
00:19:14.892 --> 00:19:16.067
Things are getting serious?

349
00:19:16.198 --> 00:19:17.721
Well. I don't know about that.

350
00:19:17.852 --> 00:19:19.767
but he definitely
comes in handy.

351
00:19:19.897 --> 00:19:21.290
A handyman?

352
00:19:21.421 --> 00:19:23.221
And he's good with
more than just his hands.

353
00:19:24.598 --> 00:19:26.469
Enjoy it.

354
00:19:26.556 --> 00:19:29.211
Relationships have a way
becoming complicated

355
00:19:29.342 --> 00:19:31.170
very quickly.

356
00:19:31.300 --> 00:19:33.998
One second you're having
the best sex of your life.

357
00:19:34.085 --> 00:19:36.218
and the next.
you want to kill him.

358
00:19:37.393 --> 00:19:39.003
Have as much fun as you can

359
00:19:39.090 --> 00:19:42.224
while you're young.
beautiful. and free.

360
00:19:42.355 --> 00:19:44.966
I intend to do just that.

361
00:19:48.796 --> 00:19:51.320
And of course. Purifoy's last
general counsel let a ton

362
00:19:51.451 --> 00:19:53.975
of work pile up once he found
out Hunter was gonna can him.

363
00:19:54.105 --> 00:19:56.195
Sounds like fun for you.

364
00:19:56.325 --> 00:19:58.762
Yeah. you know. trial by fire.

365
00:19:58.893 --> 00:20:00.460
I spoke to Deja.

366
00:20:00.547 --> 00:20:02.766
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

367
00:20:02.897 --> 00:20:06.117
She's still salty with us
for enrolling her in Excalibur.

368
00:20:06.205 --> 00:20:07.771
Well. maybe we made a mistake.

369
00:20:07.902 --> 00:20:09.164
Kid wants to be here with us.

370
00:20:09.295 --> 00:20:10.774
not at some stuffy
boarding school.

371
00:20:10.905 --> 00:20:13.299
I know. Titus. but Excalibur
is one of the best

372
00:20:13.429 --> 00:20:15.083
private academies
in the country.

373
00:20:15.170 --> 00:20:19.218
I mean. what they're doing with
STEM education is cutting edge.

374
00:20:19.348 --> 00:20:23.222
We agreed that this is what's
best for Deja right now.

375
00:20:23.352 --> 00:20:25.180
I know. but there are
perfectly good schools

376
00:20:25.311 --> 00:20:27.487
here in Atlanta.

377
00:20:27.617 --> 00:20:30.881
You know. I don't like
being away from her either.

378
00:20:31.012 --> 00:20:34.537
You know. maybe once we get settled.
and get our own shit worked out.

379
00:20:34.668 --> 00:20:37.497
then we can revisit
this conversation.

380
00:20:37.627 --> 00:20:39.977
But in the meantime. this time
is supposed to be about us

381
00:20:40.108 --> 00:20:42.806
acclimating and reconnecting.

382
00:20:46.419 --> 00:20:50.901
Can we... can we skip
the gala tonight. stay in?

383
00:20:50.988 --> 00:20:52.686
You know we can't do that.

384
00:20:52.816 --> 00:20:54.256
Hunter personally asked me
to attend.

385
00:20:56.255 --> 00:20:58.102
Well. aren't you in the least
bit anxious about being

386
00:20:58.126 --> 00:20:59.693
in the same room with Stephanie?

387
00:20:59.780 --> 00:21:01.148
I mean. we haven't
done that since...

388
00:21:01.172 --> 00:21:04.654
- Since you and me got together.
- Yeah.

389
00:21:04.785 --> 00:21:07.222
I was gonna say since
college. but. yeah. that too.

390
00:21:07.309 --> 00:21:08.963
- It's a work thing.
- It'll be fine.

391
00:21:10.617 --> 00:21:11.748
You're probably right.

392
00:21:11.879 --> 00:21:14.229
I mean. we haven't
seen her in forever.

393
00:21:14.316 --> 00:21:15.578
Yeah. forever.

394
00:21:17.014 --> 00:21:18.294
So let's just not
worry about it.

395
00:21:20.017 --> 00:21:22.803
Titus. you haven't
even finished your lunch.

396
00:21:22.890 --> 00:21:25.371
I gotta run.

397
00:21:47.567 --> 00:21:48.829
Can I help you with that?

398
00:21:52.093 --> 00:21:53.312
What took you so long?

399
00:21:55.139 --> 00:21:57.707
Got here as soon as I could.

400
00:23:15.524 --> 00:23:17.091
Alright.

401
00:23:22.618 --> 00:23:25.491
Now approaching
are the Mayor Evan Lancaster

402
00:23:25.621 --> 00:23:28.885
and the always beautiful
Stephanie Carlisle Lancaster.

403
00:23:29.016 --> 00:23:30.060
Thank you.

404
00:23:30.191 --> 00:23:31.431
Necole. tonight I'm just Evan.

405
00:23:31.540 --> 00:23:33.716
a proud husband supporting
his beautiful wife.

406
00:23:33.847 --> 00:23:35.767
Stephanie. every year.
your family's foundation

407
00:23:35.849 --> 00:23:37.024
chooses a cause.

408
00:23:37.154 --> 00:23:39.853
This year. you've chosen
the opioid epidemic.

409
00:23:39.983 --> 00:23:41.550
That's right. Necole.

410
00:23:41.637 --> 00:23:45.511
My youngest sister Tracy died
a year ago from an overdose.

411
00:23:45.598 --> 00:23:47.687
My family. like so many others
in Atlanta

412
00:23:47.817 --> 00:23:49.079
and throughout the country.

413
00:23:49.210 --> 00:23:50.994
have been
devastated by this crisis.

414
00:23:51.125 --> 00:23:52.735
So. tonight's for them.

415
00:23:52.866 --> 00:23:54.694
I couldn't think of
a more worthy cause.

416
00:23:54.781 --> 00:23:56.957
Now. before I let you go.
you look stunning.

417
00:23:57.044 --> 00:23:57.871
Thank you.

418
00:23:58.001 --> 00:23:59.263
Who are you wearing?

419
00:23:59.350 --> 00:24:02.571
I am wearing
a Bella Tru Original.

420
00:24:02.702 --> 00:24:05.835
Speaking of the rising
fashionista. here she is.

421
00:24:05.966 --> 00:24:07.358
Bella Tru. and her man.

422
00:24:07.489 --> 00:24:10.274
former Atlanta Falcons
running back Roderick Johnson!

423
00:24:10.405 --> 00:24:11.885
Good to see you again. Necole.

424
00:24:12.015 --> 00:24:13.582
Good to see you guys.

425
00:24:13.713 --> 00:24:15.932
And you look
sensational. First Lady.

426
00:24:16.063 --> 00:24:17.194
Thank you.

427
00:24:17.325 --> 00:24:19.370
But we can thank Bella.

428
00:24:19.501 --> 00:24:21.155
She's a true miracle worker.

429
00:24:21.242 --> 00:24:23.113
You give me way too much credit.

430
00:24:23.244 --> 00:24:24.264
Sweetheart.
we should get inside.

431
00:24:24.288 --> 00:24:25.768
Of course. darling.

432
00:24:25.899 --> 00:24:27.877
Well. here's hoping that we all
have a night to remember!

433
00:24:27.901 --> 00:24:30.164
Yes.

434
00:24:44.091 --> 00:24:45.745
- This is nice.
- Yeah.

435
00:24:49.836 --> 00:24:51.446
Baby. relax.

436
00:24:51.577 --> 00:24:53.230
It's all good.

437
00:24:53.361 --> 00:24:55.929
- You look beautiful.
- Thank you.

438
00:24:57.931 --> 00:24:59.715
Is... is that them?

439
00:24:59.846 --> 00:25:00.977
Yeah.

440
00:25:01.108 --> 00:25:02.109
Gird your loins.

441
00:25:08.550 --> 00:25:09.812
Good evening. Hunter.

442
00:25:09.943 --> 00:25:11.292
Titus. my man!

443
00:25:11.422 --> 00:25:13.076
- Glad you made it.
- Thank you.

444
00:25:13.207 --> 00:25:14.774
And this must be

445
00:25:14.904 --> 00:25:17.951
the whip-smart Amara
I've heard so much about.

446
00:25:18.081 --> 00:25:20.040
It's a pleasure to
meet you. Mr. Purifoy.

447
00:25:20.170 --> 00:25:22.912
Mr. Purifoy was my daddy.

448
00:25:23.043 --> 00:25:24.914
Please. call me Hunter.

449
00:25:27.308 --> 00:25:28.918
Hunter it is.

450
00:25:29.049 --> 00:25:31.181
Sweetheart. aren't you
going to introduce us?

451
00:25:31.312 --> 00:25:32.705
Of course. dear.

452
00:25:32.835 --> 00:25:34.402
Titus and Amara Hughes.

453
00:25:34.533 --> 00:25:36.752
I'd like you to meet
my beautiful wife. Juniper.

454
00:25:36.883 --> 00:25:38.101
This is my daughter. Lori.

455
00:25:39.712 --> 00:25:41.844
- Hi. So nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

456
00:25:41.931 --> 00:25:43.933
Titus. Lori works
with us at Purifoy.

457
00:25:44.064 --> 00:25:45.413
She oversees our PR department.

458
00:25:45.544 --> 00:25:47.154
So. you'll be seeing
a lot of each other.

459
00:25:47.284 --> 00:25:49.001
You're behind the company's
latest marketing campaign?

460
00:25:49.025 --> 00:25:50.636
I am.

461
00:25:50.766 --> 00:25:52.028
Isn't it fantastic?

462
00:25:54.161 --> 00:25:56.052
Excuse me. Daddy. I'm gonna
step out for a moment.

463
00:25:56.076 --> 00:25:57.425
It was very nice
meeting you both.

464
00:25:57.556 --> 00:25:59.383
- You. too.
- No problem. angel.

465
00:25:59.470 --> 00:26:01.168
Amara. Hunter tells me you work

466
00:26:01.298 --> 00:26:02.778
for the U.S. Attorney's Office.

467
00:26:02.909 --> 00:26:05.061
I was actually in the
Northern District of Birmingham

468
00:26:05.085 --> 00:26:07.261
for seven years. and then I
transferred to Atlanta

469
00:26:07.391 --> 00:26:10.656
once Titus accepted
the position at Purifoy.

470
00:26:10.743 --> 00:26:12.483
Are you from Alabama originally?

471
00:26:12.614 --> 00:26:14.877
No. actually
born and raised in Houston.

472
00:26:15.008 --> 00:26:16.618
Yeah. South Side.

473
00:26:16.749 --> 00:26:18.881
I think it's absolutely
wonderful how you've managed

474
00:26:19.012 --> 00:26:21.057
to pull yourself up
by the bootstraps.

475
00:26:21.188 --> 00:26:24.539
This country needs more of that
to bring it back to greatness.

476
00:26:24.670 --> 00:26:27.542
I'm sure your folks
back in Texas are proud.

477
00:26:27.673 --> 00:26:29.109
Extremely.

478
00:26:29.239 --> 00:26:32.112
If you'll excuse me. I'm
gonna shuffle off to the bar.

479
00:26:32.199 --> 00:26:33.896
Take your time.

480
00:26:34.027 --> 00:26:36.551
We'll get better
acquainted with Titus here.

481
00:26:36.682 --> 00:26:38.771
Yeah.

482
00:26:38.901 --> 00:26:42.078
Look who's moonlighting.

483
00:26:42.209 --> 00:26:44.864
I guess they let anybody up
in The Ducksworth Hotel?

484
00:26:44.951 --> 00:26:47.083
- What have we got here?
- Get your hands off.

485
00:26:57.137 --> 00:26:59.115
- Could use a little more sauce.
- Get the hell away

486
00:26:59.139 --> 00:27:01.489
from my stand before I forget
my home-training.

487
00:27:01.620 --> 00:27:03.186
Everything okay. Sis?

488
00:27:03.317 --> 00:27:04.710
Nothing I can't handle.

489
00:27:04.840 --> 00:27:07.364
- Mayor Lancaster!
- How's it going?

490
00:27:07.495 --> 00:27:08.888
Are you enjoying your evening?

491
00:27:09.018 --> 00:27:10.909
I always enjoy seeing
my two favorite Lancasters.

492
00:27:10.933 --> 00:27:12.152
We should hang out more.

493
00:27:12.239 --> 00:27:14.633
Kiss the crack of
my black ass. Peters.

494
00:27:16.286 --> 00:27:18.071
That could be arranged.

495
00:27:18.201 --> 00:27:20.943
Nothing like family.

496
00:27:21.074 --> 00:27:22.714
Man. am I going to miss
having her around.

497
00:27:25.731 --> 00:27:27.291
What the hell's
that supposed to mean?

498
00:27:40.615 --> 00:27:45.838
Well. the golden
Lancaster princess herself.

499
00:27:45.968 --> 00:27:47.404
Finally we meet.

500
00:27:47.491 --> 00:27:49.131
You're the last person
I expected to see

501
00:27:49.189 --> 00:27:50.625
at one of my family's events.

502
00:27:50.756 --> 00:27:52.932
Yeah. well. that
makes two of us.

503
00:27:53.062 --> 00:27:55.499
Let me guess. your parents
thought attending a fundraiser

504
00:27:55.630 --> 00:27:57.414
fighting Atlanta's opioid crisis

505
00:27:57.545 --> 00:27:59.068
would make them look less
guilty?

506
00:27:59.199 --> 00:28:01.767
If I didn't know any better.

507
00:28:01.897 --> 00:28:04.552
I'd say it was your mom
standing here in front of me.

508
00:28:04.683 --> 00:28:06.380
My mother
is doing her job by going

509
00:28:06.467 --> 00:28:08.208
after Purifoy Pharmaceuticals.

510
00:28:08.338 --> 00:28:10.863
Your family's job is
to sit around figuring out

511
